These are the major site security measures:

¿	Six-foot minimum height chain-link fence surrounds the site
¿	Facility main entrance is locked. Any visitors need to be buzzed in to access the site and employees have key cards which will unlock the main gate for entry. 
¿	The Plant is staffed 24 hours a day, 365 days a year.
¿	All other gates are locked but may be opened in the event of emergency egress from the inside.
¿	Warning signs

It is the policy of Springdale Energy to assure the safe operation of the facility which is designed and built to good engineering practices that incorporate methods or principles in accordance with applicable industry standards.  Some of these standards include ASME Code for Power Piping, B31.1, and ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code, Section VIII.   

Five Year Accident History

There have been no reportable accidents in the past five years.  

Emergency Response

There is a written emergency action plan that is coordinated with the Allegheny County Health Department, the Springdale LEPC and the local fire departments.  All site personnel are trained only to the Hazmat Awareness Response Level which is identify/notify. In the case of an emergency, all HAZWOPER responses will be performed by off-site response personnel.        

